<paragraph blockId="9.[151,653,386,412]" box="[151,653,386,412]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,653,386,412]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,653,386,412]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName authority="Krishnankutty &amp; Viraktamath, 2008" authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,356,386,412]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,356,386,412]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Cofana spiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[364,458,386,412]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation box="[473,556,386,412]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,211,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-50@2.[151,1436,197,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–2, Cofana bidentata n.sp., male &amp; female; 3, Cofana lineata (Distant); 4, Cofana nigrilinea (Stål); 5, Cofana spectra (Distant); 6, Cofana spiculata sp. nov.; 7, Cofana subvirescens (Stål); 8, Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133662/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[571,645,386,412]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–51" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[192,1382,205,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[180,1392,194,1774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 44–51. Cofana spiculata sp. nov., 44, head; 45, lateral view of aedeagus; 46, caudal view of aedeagus; 47, dorsal view of pygofer; 48, ventral view of subgenital plate; 49, male abdominal apodeme; 50, dorsal view of style; 51, lateral view of apex of style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133672/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">44–51</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,461,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
Length: male, 6.5–6.8 mm. Dark brown species. Crown with anterior margin narrowly pointed. Crown with median apical black spot and two medium sized round spots each near lateral clypeal sutures that extending to ocelli, disk of crown with central rhomboid large black spot. Pronotum with distinct central longitudinal brown line extending to scutellum, anterior portion with discontinuous brown patches arranged transversely and posterior margin with two pale black round spots on either side of central line (
<figureCitation box="[1151,1240,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–51" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[192,1382,205,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[180,1392,194,1774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 44–51. Cofana spiculata sp. nov., 44, head; 45, lateral view of aedeagus; 46, caudal view of aedeagus; 47, dorsal view of pygofer; 48, ventral view of subgenital plate; 49, male abdominal apodeme; 50, dorsal view of style; 51, lateral view of apex of style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133672/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
). Clypellus with central pale brown longitudinal line. Genae with brown markings. Forewing dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[1201,1272,661,687]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[151,269,1910,1934]" captionTargetBox="[159,1423,211,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-50@2.[151,1436,197,1883]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. 1–2, Cofana bidentata n.sp., male &amp; female; 3, Cofana lineata (Distant); 4, Cofana nigrilinea (Stål); 5, Cofana spectra (Distant); 6, Cofana spiculata sp. nov.; 7, Cofana subvirescens (Stål); 8, Cofana unimaculata (Signoret)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133662/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,461,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[197,376,701,726]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with caudo-dorsal angle slightly produced dorsally, caudal margin almost straight (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,741,767]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–51" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[192,1382,205,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[180,1392,194,1774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 44–51. Cofana spiculata sp. nov., 44, head; 45, lateral view of aedeagus; 46, caudal view of aedeagus; 47, dorsal view of pygofer; 48, ventral view of subgenital plate; 49, male abdominal apodeme; 50, dorsal view of style; 51, lateral view of apex of style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133672/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
). Style in dorsal view stouter than in 
<emphasis box="[685,809,741,766]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Young" authorityYear="1979" box="[685,804,741,766]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineata">C. lineata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
apex pigmented, in lateral view bluntly pointed (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 44–51" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[192,1382,205,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[180,1392,194,1774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 44–51. Cofana spiculata sp. nov., 44, head; 45, lateral view of aedeagus; 46, caudal view of aedeagus; 47, dorsal view of pygofer; 48, ventral view of subgenital plate; 49, male abdominal apodeme; 50, dorsal view of style; 51, lateral view of apex of style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133672/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 50, 51</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft in lateral view broadly flattened, triangular, longer than dorsal apodeme, dorsal margin of shaft straight and smooth, ventral margin denticulate towards base; dorsal apodeme not well developed near apex, close to shaft along its length (
<figureCitation box="[652,742,861,887]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–51" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[192,1382,205,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[180,1392,194,1774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 44–51. Cofana spiculata sp. nov., 44, head; 45, lateral view of aedeagus; 46, caudal view of aedeagus; 47, dorsal view of pygofer; 48, ventral view of subgenital plate; 49, male abdominal apodeme; 50, dorsal view of style; 51, lateral view of apex of style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133672/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
); in caudal view shaft broad near base, abruptly narrowed beyond mid length (
<figureCitation box="[388,476,901,927]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–51" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[192,1382,205,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[180,1392,194,1774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 44–51. Cofana spiculata sp. nov., 44, head; 45, lateral view of aedeagus; 46, caudal view of aedeagus; 47, dorsal view of pygofer; 48, ventral view of subgenital plate; 49, male abdominal apodeme; 50, dorsal view of style; 51, lateral view of apex of style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133672/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 46</figureCitation>
). Abdominal apodemes long, slender reaching mid length of fourth segment (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 44–51" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[192,1382,205,1690]" captionTargetId="figure-61@10.[180,1392,194,1774]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 44–51. Cofana spiculata sp. nov., 44, head; 45, lateral view of aedeagus; 46, caudal view of aedeagus; 47, dorsal view of pygofer; 48, ventral view of subgenital plate; 49, male abdominal apodeme; 50, dorsal view of style; 51, lateral view of apex of style." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5133672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5133672/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,461,1327]" box="[197,408,981,1007]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,461,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[197,329,1021,1046]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet, 
<emphasis box="[601,716,1021,1046]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krishnankutty &amp; Viraktamath" authorityYear="2008" box="[601,711,1021,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cofana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spiculata">spiculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
refers to spiny projections along the posterior margin of aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
